# Axis 5 — capture + resume, same host, state-threaded

A deep handler whose arms return functions, threading an accumulator through
`resume(())(s + v)` — the in-process precursor of the durable `save()`/`run()`
idiom. Each `emit` suspends; the handler resumes with the running state. This is
the same-host, same-process capture/resume the durable capsule generalises to
cross-process and cross-host (both pending the DurableValue codec).

```scalascript
effect Yield:
  def emit(v: Int): Unit

def prog(): Int =
  Yield.emit(10)
  Yield.emit(20)
  0

val threaded = handle(prog()) {
  case Yield.emit(v, resume) => (s: Int) => resume(())(s + v)
  case Return(x) => (s: Int) => x + s
}
println(threaded(0))
```
